Save — this change disables firewall-based public IP access.


Azure Cosmos DB
Built-in policy: Azure Cosmos DB should disable public network access

Definition ID: 797b37f7-06b8-444c-b1ad-fc62867f335a
Effect: Audit, Deny, or Modify – ensures properties.publicNetworkAccess = Disabled for all Cosmos DB accounts.


Implementation Recommendations

Recommendation:
Assign the respective built-in policies at the management group or subscription level with effect set to Deny or Modify based on your governance model.

	Modify: Automatically corrects noncompliant resources.
	Deny: Prevents any creation or update that would enable public network access.


Manual only: While turning off public network access manually in the portal is possible, it doesn’t prevent future misconfiguration or ensure compliance across large environments.
